The study of world religions is among the most important and humanizing of intellectual pursuits — it asks us to take seriously how billions of human beings across history and cultures have understood the deepest questions of existence: Who are we? Where do we come from? How should we live? What happens after death? From a Christian perspective, the study of world religions is not merely academic but an act of charity toward our neighbors: to understand their faith is to understand them, and to understand them is the first step toward sharing the truth and love of the Gospel.
